Welcome to nishamadhulika.com

00:00:08.148 --> 00:00:10.789
We have already prepared matar mushroom.

00:00:11.219 --> 00:00:14.617
Green chana is also available in abundance in market.

00:00:15.422 --> 00:00:17.078
They are also called cholia.

00:00:17.350 --> 00:00:28.498
Today we will make cholia mushroom sabzi with different and delectable flavor.

00:00:28.805 --> 00:00:35.101
Let’s see what all ingredients are required for making cholia mushroom.

00:00:35.601 --> 00:00:37.976
Mushroom - 200 grams

00:00:38.499 --> 00:00:42.296
Cholia - 200 grams

00:00:42.758 --> 00:00:43.859
Tomatoes - 3

00:00:44.125 --> 00:00:45.352
Green chilly - 2

00:00:45.695 --> 00:00:47.266
Ginger - ½ inch baton

00:00:48.117 --> 00:00:51.609
Green coriander - 2 tbsp (finely chopped)

00:00:51.883 --> 00:00:53.938
Cashew nuts - 2-3 tbsp

00:00:54.210 --> 00:00:56.226
Oil - 2-3 tbsp

00:00:56.602 --> 00:00:58.508
Cumin seeds - ½ tsp

00:00:59.086 --> 00:01:00.547
Asafoetida - 1 pinch

00:01:01.398 --> 00:01:04.616
Garam masala - less then ¼ tsp

00:01:04.977 --> 00:01:07.602
Turmeric powder - ¼ tsp

00:01:07.836 --> 00:01:10.602
Red chilly powder - ¼ tsp

00:01:11.078 --> 00:01:13.461
Coriander powder - 1 tsp

00:01:13.859 --> 00:01:18.062
Salt - ¾ tsp (as per taste)

00:01:19.320 --> 00:01:31.328
For making cholia matar sabzi firstly grind tomato, green chilly, ginger and cashew nuts for making a fine paste.

00:01:42.390 --> 00:01:43.625
Now we will make sabzi.

00:01:43.648 --> 00:01:50.906
Preheat a pan and add oil into it.

00:01:54.398 --> 00:02:13.906
When oil gets heated add cumin seeds, asafoetida, coriander powder and turmeric powder.

00:02:15.906 --> 00:02:17.797
Sauté for while.

00:02:19.327 --> 00:02:28.304
Now add tomato-ginger-cashew nuts paste in the pan.

00:02:28.882 --> 00:02:31.343
Also add red chilly.

00:02:32.313 --> 00:02:44.593
If you wish to add onion and garlic then after suating cumin seeds add finely chopped onion and 3-4 cloves in the pan.

00:02:44.750 --> 00:02:47.922
Roast until onions turns little pinkish in color.

00:02:48.070 --> 00:02:55.375
Then add paste and sauté until oil starts separating from the masala.

00:02:56.586 --> 00:03:03.695
Meanwhile cut mushroom.

00:03:04.210 --> 00:03:09.625
There is no need to cut mushrooms, just clean them a cloth.

00:03:21.124 --> 00:03:36.984
Masala is ready; now mix cholia and salt into it.

00:03:41.068 --> 00:03:47.834
For better flavor we have used cashew nuts for making gravy.

00:03:48.375 --> 00:04:02.390
We can use peanuts, sesame seeds, soaked khas khas, melon seeds or plain gravy with tomato-onion only.

00:04:06.304 --> 00:04:15.890
For better understanding of making gravies logon to nishamadhulika.com

00:04:18.662 --> 00:04:21.859
Now add ½ cup water.

00:04:22.063 --> 00:04:26.586
Cover and cook until chana becomes tender.

00:04:39.031 --> 00:04:42.149
Stir after every 2 minutes.

00:04:50.851 --> 00:04:55.155
Make 6-8 pieces of one mushroom.

00:05:19.593 --> 00:05:24.507
Within 10 minutes chana become tender.

00:05:32.139 --> 00:05:44.250
Now add mushrooms, garam masala and green coriander.

00:05:48.227 --> 00:05:49.531
Mix all ingredients

00:05:50.484 --> 00:05:56.749
If you wish to have more thin consistency of gravy then add some more water.

00:06:12.492 --> 00:06:25.421
Now cover and cook for 2 minutes on low flame so that spices get absorbed in mushroom as well.

00:06:32.172 --> 00:06:39.125
Sabzi is ready; take it out in a bowl.

00:06:44.515 --> 00:06:49.335
Garnish with green coriander leaves.

00:06:52.429 --> 00:06:57.796
Lip smacking and mouth drooling cholia mushroom is ready.

00:06:58.164 --> 00:07:03.742
Serve with chapatti, parantha or naan.

00:07:04.141 --> 00:07:11.195
